techmeme.title: Avantos, which develops an AI-native client management system for financial institutions, raised a $25M Series A led by Bessemer, bringing total funding to $35M (Minh Le/Tech in Asia)
OpenAI says users aged 18-24 account for ~50% and under-30s represent 80% of ChatGPT usage in India; Indians use ChatGPT mostly for work (Ivan Mehta/TechCrunch)
Pepper, which provides a digital storefront for independent food distributors, raised a $50M Series C led by Lead Edge, bringing its total funding to $100M (Chris Metinko/Axios)
Scott Myers, the SVP of Snap's AR glasses unit Specs, leaves after six years; sources say Myers left after a "blow-up" with Evan Spiegel over Snap's strategy (Alex Heath/Sources)
Sources: SoftBank plans to form a consortium to build a $33B power plant in Ohio, set to produce 9.2 GW for AI data centers, as part of the US-Japan trade deal (Nikkei Asia)
